Career Opportunities



 
Senior Compliance Manager
Penn Capital is seeking a Senior Compliance Manager who will be responsible for the day-to-day compliance functions relating to the investment advisory business of an SEC registered investment adviser, including testing and surveillance to ensure the adequacy of policies and procedures and the effectiveness of their implementation. Must be knowledgeable about compliance programs operated pursuant to the Investment Adviser Acts of 1940 and Investment Company Act of 1940. 
Responsibilities
Supervise the firm’s compliance program
Design and performing compliance tests, periodic reviews, and internal audits
Maintain compliance calendar and ensure recurring tasks are tracked, completed, and recorded
Review/approve marketing materials, including RFP responses and developing disclosures
Conduct periodic due diligence in vendors and service providers
Identify and manage compliance/operational risks; maintain the firm’s risk matrix
Update or coordinate regulatory filings and disclosures (e.g., Form ADV, Form U4, etc.)
Develop compliance education tools for employees
Certifications, and case management; create reports to evidence archived activities
Oversight of portfolio management compliance, client guidelines, restrictions and trading activity, including best execution
Conduct and coordinate Rule 206(4)-7 and Rule 38(a)-1 annual compliance reviews
Coordinate regulatory examinations and client due diligence reviews
Collaborate with members of the firm and senior management; participating on firm committees and coordinating audits and other meetings
Stay abreast of applicable regulatory developments and make relevant updates to policies and procedures
Provide feedback and input to assist in continued development of program efficiencies
Reporting any potential or perceived violations of applicable laws, rules or firm policies
Collaborate with firm’s Series 24 Supervising Principal on registered representative activities and reporting
Other tasks and projects as assigned
Requiremements
Bachelors or equivalent college degree
5 years’ industry related compliance experience
In-depth understanding of SEC, FINRA and state rules that govern advisors, registered funds, private funds and registered representative supervision
Excellent analytical, reasoning and problem-solving skills
Ability to understand, interpret and communicate complex rules and regulations and communicate to clients and internal staff, including management
Serve a critical role as primary compliance point-of-contact for unaffiliated FINRA member firm that registered representatives are associated with
Strong writing skills and presentation skills
Ability to skillfully and professionally interact with clients and senior management
High attention to detail
Ability to prioritize workflow and meet deadlines 
  Only submitted resumes will be considered
Administrative Associate 
Penn Capital is seeking an Administrative Associate to assist the Executive Administrative Associate in managing front office related activities. S/he shall assist in greeting guests, answering phones, and providing a positive guest experience. Additional responsibilities include clerical and administrative related tasks, light bookkeeping, and occasional marketing team support. 
Essential Functions and Responsibilities
Guest Management and Suite Operations - Greet guests in a professional manner; assist in providing a positive experience at the firm
Phone System Management
Various clerical responsibilities including, but not limited to, scanning, filing, and other administrative duties on an as needed basis
Ensure phone calls and general mailbox messages are directed accordingly
Vendor management
Management/Distribution of firm wide correspondence
Administrative tasks for senior management including calendar management and ad hoc requests 
Desired Knowledge and Experience
Bachelor's degree
Strong working knowledge of Microsoft Office
Strong work ethic and ability to work in a team environment
Excellent phone etiquette and outstaning customer service orientation
Professional demeanor
Punctual
Strong ability to work with with all levels of internal management and staff, as well as external clients and vendors  
Only submitted resumes will be considered
Contact Information: To apply for a position at Penn Capital please forward your cover letter, including salary or compensation expectations, along with a professional resume to employment@penncapital.com. Only submissions with an attached resume will be considered. 
Penn Capital is an Equal Opportunity Employer
 










