Lawson Products, Inc. (LAWS) EPS Estimated At $0.09; Penn Capital Management Co Raised By $1.28 Million Its Xpo Logistics (XPO) Position


					
						July 19, 2017 - By Adrian Erickson


 Analysts expect Lawson Products, Inc. (NASDAQ:LAWS) to report $0.09 EPS on July, 27 before the open.They anticipate $0.07 EPS change or 350.00% from last quarter’s $0.02 EPS. LAWS’s profit would be $780,231 giving it 57.78 P/E if the $0.09 EPS is correct. After having $0.09 EPS previously, Lawson Products, Inc.’s analysts see 0.00% EPS growth. It closed at $20.8 lastly. It is down 4.61% since July 19, 2016 and is uptrending. It has underperformed by 12.09% the S&P500.
Penn Capital Management Co Inc increased Xpo Logistics Inc (XPO) stake by 69.11% reported in 2016Q4 SEC filing. Penn Capital Management Co Inc acquired 51,276 shares as Xpo Logistics Inc (XPO)’s stock rose 7.25%. The Penn Capital Management Co Inc holds 125,472 shares with $3.15M value, up from 74,196 last quarter. Xpo Logistics Inc now has $6.92 billion valuation. It closed at $61.22 lastly. It is down 103.27% since July 19, 2016 and is uptrending. It has outperformed by 86.57% the S&P500.






Penn Capital Management Co Inc decreased Pinnacle Entmt Inc stake by 90,712 shares to 777,761 valued at $12.18 million in 2016Q4. It also reduced Impax Laboratories Inc (NASDAQ:IPXL) stake by 279,970 shares and now owns 156,429 shares. Medidata Solutions Inc (Prn) was reduced too. 
Among 14 analysts covering XPO Logistics (NYSE:XPO), 14 have Buy rating, 0 Sell and 0 Hold. Therefore 100% are positive. XPO Logistics had 35 analyst reports since August 7, 2015 according to SRatingsIntel. Oppenheimer maintained the stock with “Buy” rating in Tuesday, July 11 report. The rating was initiated by Susquehanna on Tuesday, December 20 with “Positive”. Cowen & Co maintained XPO Logistics Inc (NYSE:XPO) rating on Friday, February 26. Cowen & Co has “Outperform” rating and $36 target. The company was maintained on Tuesday, December 6 by Cowen & Co. Citigroup maintained XPO Logistics Inc (NYSE:XPO) on Thursday, April 14 with “Buy” rating. JP Morgan maintained the stock with “Overweight” rating in Friday, August 5 report. Oppenheimer maintained the stock with “Buy” rating in Monday, July 17 report. Oppenheimer maintained XPO Logistics Inc (NYSE:XPO) on Wednesday, September 30 with “Outperform” rating. The stock of XPO Logistics Inc (NYSE:XPO) has “Outperform” rating given on Monday, September 14 by Cowen & Co. The stock has “Overweight” rating by JP Morgan on Monday, July 11.
Investors sentiment decreased to 1.34 in 2016 Q4. Its down 0.25, from 1.59 in 2016Q3. It worsened, as 12 investors sold XPO shares while 77 reduced holdings. 46 funds opened positions while 73 raised stakes. 74.02 million shares or 1.25% less from 74.95 million shares in 2016Q3 were reported. 3,670 were reported by Creative Planning. Sunbelt Securities accumulated 100 shares. First Western Cap Management has 12,000 shares for 0.28% of their portfolio. Fil Ltd owns 0% invested in XPO Logistics Inc (NYSE:XPO) for 35,400 shares. Da Davidson owns 4,819 shares. Winch Advisory Services Ltd Com, Wisconsin-based fund reported 390 shares. Eventide Asset Limited Liability Com invested in 1.13M shares. 3,872 are owned by Zurcher Kantonalbank (Zurich Cantonalbank). The United Kingdom-based Cantab Cap Ptnrs Llp has invested 0% in XPO Logistics Inc (NYSE:XPO). 115 are owned by Massmutual Tru Fsb Adv. Steinberg Asset Mngmt Limited Liability Company has invested 1.17% in XPO Logistics Inc (NYSE:XPO). Qci Asset Mngmt Ny has invested 0% in XPO Logistics Inc (NYSE:XPO). The Texas-based Next Fin Group Incorporated has invested 0% in XPO Logistics Inc (NYSE:XPO). Dimensional Fund Ltd Partnership holds 0.06% of its portfolio in XPO Logistics Inc (NYSE:XPO) for 2.99M shares. Parametric Port Associates Ltd Llc invested in 102,142 shares or 0.01% of the stock.
Since March 3, 2017, it had 2 buys, and 3 selling transactions for $28,214 activity. 1,591 shares valued at $43,301 were sold by McCarthy Shane on Friday, March 3. $20,132 worth of Lawson Products, Inc. (NASDAQ:LAWS) shares were bought by King John Bryan. JENKINS NEIL E sold $120,581 worth of Lawson Products, Inc. (NASDAQ:LAWS) on Monday, June 12.
Lawson Products, Inc. is a distributor of services and products the industrial, commercial, institutional and government maintenance, repair and activities market. The company has market cap of $180.32 million. The Company’s product categories include fastening systems, fluid power, specialty chemicals, cutting tools and abrasives, electrical, aftermarket automotive supplies, safety, welding and metal repair, and other. It currently has negative earnings. The Firm supplies a range of automotive products, including body hardware, body shop, brake/wheel, fleet/truck, repair harness assembly and other parts.



