Penn Capital Management Co Lifted Its Covenant Transn Group (CVTI) Position; Harman International Industries (HAR) Sentiment Is 0.77


					

						July 18, 2017 - By Louis Casey

Penn Capital Management Co Inc increased Covenant Transn Group Inc (CVTI) stake by 40.26% reported in 2016Q4 SEC filing. Penn Capital Management Co Inc acquired 143,457 shares as Covenant Transn Group Inc (CVTI)’s stock declined 15.27%. The Penn Capital Management Co Inc holds 499,749 shares with $9.67M value, up from 356,292 last quarter. Covenant Transn Group Inc now has $303.76M valuation. The stock declined 3.94% or $0.67 reaching $16.32 on the news. About 61,839 shares traded. Covenant Transportation Group, Inc. (NASDAQ:CVTI) has declined 12.60% since July 18, 2016 and is downtrending. It has underperformed by 29.30% the S&P500.
Harman International Industries, Incorporated is engaged in the designing and engineering of connected products and solutions for automakers, clients and enterprises, including connected car systems, audio and visual products, enterprise automation solutions and connected services. The company has market cap of $7.79 billion. The Company’s divisions include Connected Car, Lifestyle Audio, Professional Solutions, Connected Services and Other. It has a 22.04 P/E ratio. The Connected Car segment designs, makes and markets connected car systems for vehicle applications.






 It is down 0.00% since July 18, 2016 and is . It has underperformed by 16.70% the S&P500.
Edinburgh Partners Ltd holds 13.74% of its portfolio in Harman International Industries Inc for 587,660 shares. Burren Capital Advisors Ltd owns 33,450 shares or 12.52% of their US portfolio. Moreover, Kellner Capital Llc has 6.36% invested in the company for 101,200 shares. The Pennsylvania-based Gardner Lewis Asset Management L P has invested 5.63% in the stock. Water Island Capital Llc, a New York-based fund reported 555,947 shares.
Since January 1, 0001, it had 0 buys, and 1 sale for $970,812 activity. 
Investors sentiment increased to 1.41 in 2016 Q4. Its up 0.22, from 1.19 in 2016Q3. It improved, as 13 investors sold CVTI shares while 21 reduced holdings. 18 funds opened positions while 30 raised stakes. 10.12 million shares or 8.25% less from 11.03 million shares in 2016Q3 were reported. Northern Tru holds 143,499 shares. Blackrock Advsrs Ltd Liability Corporation has 0% invested in Covenant Transportation Group, Inc. (NASDAQ:CVTI) for 6,593 shares. The New York-based Blackrock has invested 0% in Covenant Transportation Group, Inc. (NASDAQ:CVTI). Guggenheim Capital Limited Liability Corp holds 0.01% or 154,300 shares. 32,700 are owned by California Employees Retirement System. Bnp Paribas Arbitrage has invested 0% in Covenant Transportation Group, Inc. (NASDAQ:CVTI). Mutual Of America Cap Ltd Liability Company owns 424,522 shares or 0.15% of their US portfolio. Prescott Gru Inc Mgmt holds 0.4% or 99,200 shares in its portfolio. New York State Common Retirement Fund holds 11,800 shares. Pier Cap Ltd Limited Liability Company has invested 0.57% in Covenant Transportation Group, Inc. (NASDAQ:CVTI). Penn Capital Mngmt Com invested in 499,749 shares or 0.61% of the stock. State Street invested in 174,881 shares or 0% of the stock. Blackrock Invest Mgmt Ltd Liability Company holds 50,013 shares. Alliancebernstein Ltd Partnership stated it has 1.21 million shares. Fmr Limited Liability Corporation has 461,300 shares.
Penn Capital Management Co Inc decreased Nanostring Technologies Inc (NASDAQ:NSTG) stake by 114,237 shares to 27,285 valued at $608,000 in 2016Q4. It also reduced Cobiz Financial Inc (NASDAQ:COBZ) stake by 124,393 shares and now owns 649,683 shares. Kirklands Inc (NASDAQ:KIRK) was reduced too. 
